post.description:
Takes a list of question/answer as input to determine the legal text to put on the transport document for the provided dangerous goods item (ADR). Questions and answers are specified using their unique identifier (see the References chapter to get the full list of available questions and answers).

The response will contain the list of previously answered questions with their responses and, either the next question to be answered, or a list of errors if this list of previously answered questions is not correct/consistent. If no questions are sent, then the first question in the question tree will be sent back as the next question to be answered.

## Example of Requests/Responses workflow:

### First request to start

```json
{
  "languages": [
    "en"
  ]
}
```

### First response

```json
{
  "nextQuestion": {
    "questionId": "0",
    "questionLabel": "Use default text or specific text on transport document?",
    "answers": [
      {
        "answerId": "0",
        "answerLabel": "Use default text"
      },
      {
        "answerId": "1",
        "answerLabel": "Use specific text"
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

### Second request as an answer to the first question

```json
{
  "languages": [
    "en"
  ],
  "questions": [
    {
      "questionId": "0",
      "answerId": "0"
    }
  ]
}
```

### Second and final response

```json
{
  "previousQuestions": [
    {
      "questionId": "0",
      "answerId": "0"
    }
  ],
  "resultTexts": {
    "lang": "en",
    "value": "UN 0478 SUBSTANCES, EXPLOSIVE, N.O.S. (technical name), 1.3G, (C5000D)"
  }
}
```
